1:
"People need to work hard on this earth like soldiers do;
\q1 all during the time that we are alive, we need to work as hard as any hired worker.
\q1

3:
God has given to me many months in which I think that it is useless to remain alive;
\q1 he has assigned to me many nights during which I feel miserable.
\q1

6:
My days pass as quickly as a weaver's shuttle;
\q2 when one day ends, I never expect that things will be better the next day.
\q1

7:
God, do not forget that my life is as short as a single breath;
\q2 I think that I will never again experience being happy.
\q1

9:
Like a cloud passes and disappears,
\q2 people die and descend to the place where dead people are, and they do not return;
\q1

11:
So I will not be silent;
\q2 while I am suffering, I will speak;
\q1 I will complain to God about what has happened to me
\q2 because I am very angry.
\q1

13:
When I lie down at night, I say to myself, 'I will go to sleep and stop suffering;
\q2 my pain will be less while I am sleeping.'
\q1

14:
But then you give me dreams that cause me to be afraid;
\q2 you give me visions that terrify me;
\q1

17:
We human beings are not very important;
\q2 so why do you pay so much attention to us ?
\q1
